      "id": "https://sarahstech.blog/comments/remote-work-comment-2",
      "published": "2025-05-20T18:10:00Z",
      "content": "The burnout stats are alarming but not surprising. I think part of the problem is that managers haven't adapted their expectations to remote work. They're measuring presence instead of output, which leads to performative 'always online' behavior. We need better management training for remote teams.",
